Method Detail

select

<T> T select(Class<T> type,
             Iterable<T> candidates)
         throws IllegalArgumentException
Given a set of candidates, select an appropriate one. Even if there are candidates this method may throw IllegalArgumentException if there was no suitable candidate.

Parameters:
type - the type of items.
candidates - candidates up for selection, where one should be picked. There might also be no suitable candidate, in which case an exception should be thrown.
Returns:
a suitable candidate among all available.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if no suitable candidate was found.
